# CQ2 — When no explicit permission applies to a role, can that absence be
#        identified (the structural basis for closed-world default-deny)?
# Competency check: can the ontology determine, for any stakeholder role,
# whether an AccessPolicy applies to it? A role with no applicable policy is
# the configuration under which the R09 default-deny rule denies access.
# This query interrogates the modeled structure. Enforcing the deny outcome
# itself is the job of the R09 CONSTRUCT rule.
# Evaluate over: core ontology + role taxonomy + example policies.
# Expected: every role in the taxonomy listed with "yes" or "no" according to
# whether a policy applies, with at least one role of each kind present.

PREFIX dpp-ac: <http://w3id.org/dpp/access-control#>
PREFIX rdfs:   <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?role (IF(BOUND(?policy), "yes", "no") AS ?hasApplicablePolicy)
WHERE {
    ?role rdfs:subClassOf* dpp-ac:Role .
    FILTER (?role != dpp-ac:Role)
    OPTIONAL { ?policy dpp-ac:appliesToRole ?role }
}
ORDER BY ?role
